Olympus Board Votes to Replace Michael C. Woodford as President

-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 
2011-10-14T00:42:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/olympus-board-votes-to-replace-michael-c-woodford-as-president.html
Olympus Corp. (7733) ’s board of management
voted to replace Michael C. Woodford as President due to
disagreements over his method of management.  The Japanese optical-equipment maker said it would be
“difficult” to fulfill its business plan under his management,
in a statement to the Tokyo Stock Exchange today.  Chairman Tsuyoshi Kikukawa will double as president, the
statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
